.br
.RS
.PP
The key representation


.RE
.B
\fBopenssh_key_v1_attributes() :: [{atom(), term()}].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Types for the experimental implementation of the \fIopenssh_key_v1\fR format.


.RE
.B
\fBoptimize_key_lookup() :: {optimize, time | space}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Make the handling of large files fast by setting \fItime\fR, but this will use more memory. The \fIspace\fR variant shrinks the memory requirements, but with a higher time consumption.

.PP
To set it, set the option \fI{key_cb, {ssh_file, [{optimize,TimeOrSpace}]}\fR in the call of ssh:connect/3, \fIssh:daemon/2\fR or similar function call that initiates an ssh connection.


.RE
.B
\fBpubkey_passphrase_client_options() ::\fR
\fB          {dsa_pass_phrase, string()} |\fR
\fB          {rsa_pass_phrase, string()} |\fR
\fB          {ecdsa_pass_phrase, string()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
If the user's DSA, RSA or ECDSA key is protected by a passphrase, it can be supplied with those options.

.PP
Note that EdDSA passhrases (Curves 25519 and 448) are not implemented.


.RE
.B
\fBsystem_dir_daemon_option() :: {system_dir, string()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the system directory.


.RE
